======================================================================
EACH NUMBER THROUGH THE TAU LENS
kind-pasteur-2026-03-14-S106g
======================================================================

  THE TAU COORDINATE SYSTEM:
  Each number n has:
    altitude = log_tau(n)
    heartbeat = floor(altitude / 3) = which period it's in
    phase = altitude mod 3 = where within the period
    phase ≈ 0: near a period boundary (like 1, 6, 38, 241)
    phase ≈ 1: near a choice point (like 2, 11, 71, 443)
    phase ≈ 2: near a cycle point (like 3, 21, 131)

  Heartbeat 0: tau^0 to tau^3 ≈ [1, 6.2]     (the foundation)
  Heartbeat 1: tau^3 to tau^6 ≈ [6.2, 38.7]  (the first cycle)
  Heartbeat 2: tau^6 to tau^9 ≈ [38.7, 240.9] (the expansion)
  Heartbeat 3: tau^9 to tau^12 ≈ [240.9, 1499] (the large scale)

